{
  "text": "We next probed the ability of various ␣-synuclein mutants to promote SNARE-complex assembly similar to WT ␣-synuclein. To analyze the effect of ␣-synuclein mutants on SNARE-complex assembly, we expressed the various ␣-synuclein proteins by lentiviral delivery in cultured neurons obtained from triple ␣/␤/␥-synuclein KO mice. We then assayed SNARE-complex assembly using two independent methods: (1) immunoblotting of SDS-resistant SNARE-complexes on SDS-polyacrylamide gels [CITATION_1] and (2) coimmunoprecipitating the SNARE proteins synaptobrevin-2 and SNAP-25 with antibodies to the SNAREprotein syntaxin-1 (Figs. 5, 6 ). For both assays, we used quantitative immunoblotting with 125 I-labeled secondary antibodies to measure the levels of the indicated proteins.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "45690449"
